[
  {
    "data": {},
    "type": "paragraph",
    "children": [
      {
        "text": "You can allow your users to configure column visibility, order, and width by themselves."
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "data": {},
    "type": "paragraph",
    "children": [
      {
        "text": "Provide the "
      },
      {
        "text": "showColumnsConfig={true}",
        "uui-richTextEditor-code": true
      },
      {
        "text": " prop to enable the columns' config dialog. The config button will appear in the last column."
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "data": {},
    "type": "paragraph",
    "children": [
      {
        "text": "For allowing columns to resize and reorder, use "
      },
      {
        "text": "allowColumnsResizing={true}",
        "uui-richTextEditor-code": true
      },
      {
        "text": " and "
      },
      {
        "text": "allowColumnsReordering={true}",
        "uui-richTextEditor-code": true
      },
      {
        "text": " props.  Additionally, you can individually allow or disable resizing for each column by using the "
      },
      {
        "text": "allowResizing",
        "uui-richTextEditor-code": true
      },
      {
        "text": " field in "
      },
      {
        "text": "DataColumnProps",
        "uui-richTextEditor-code": true
      },
      {
        "text": "."
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "data": {},
    "type": "paragraph",
    "children": [
      {
        "text": "Hint",
        "uui-richTextEditor-bold": true
      },
      {
        "text": ": To display a column config button in your table, you need to explicitly add last column with empty caption and  "
      },
      {
        "text": "fix:'right'",
        "uui-richTextEditor-code": true
      },
      {
        "text": " to provide the required space for this button."
      }
    ]
  }
]